name: Empty Void - PreBETA
description: This is the very first version of EMPTY VOID ever made. Compiled in Scratch and made to run at a measly 30FPS in 384 x 216px. The game was first known to be created in late 2019 as a proof of concept for open-world adventure games in Scratch. Using a series of lists and points for collision detection, and a small variable inventory system with non-modifiable "structs" used for item data.
